excerpt: Park at a Thai temple with more than 1,500 butterflies, plus art & educational information.
detail_description: Mariposario de Benalmádena-Butterfly Park is a captivating attraction that offers an up-close encounter with over 1,500 butterflies of 150 different species. Nestled in the scenic Benalmadena Pueblo, the park features breeding rooms where visitors can witness the enchanting life cycle of these colorful creatures, from caterpillar to chrysalis.
name: Mariposario de Benalmádena-Butterfly Park
address: C. Muerdago, s/n, 29639 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Family-friendly exhibits with a variety of sea creatures (most offer play areas & group packages).
detail_description: Sea Life Benalmádena is a top-notch aquarium situated at the entrance to the Benalmadena Marina, offering an array of family-friendly exhibits showcasing various sea creatures. Visitors can marvel at legendary sharks, the world's largest Japanese spider crab, and green turtles. The interactive aquarium provides touch pools, a walk-through tunnel, and feeding demonstrations for an immersive experience.
name: Sea Life Benalmádena
address: Av. del Puerto Deportivo, s/n, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Shows by marine animals, birds & snakes, plus guided tours & feeding sessions in the penguinarium.
detail_description: Selwo Marina is a marine animal park in Benalmadena, offering shows featuring dolphins, birds, and snakes. Visitors can enjoy guided tours and feeding sessions in the penguinarium. The park is home to various plant and animal species from around the world, including penguins, sea lions, exotic birds, crocodiles, piranhas, anacondas, and more.
name: Selwo Marina
address: Parque de la Paloma s/n, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Spacious urban park featuring an artificial pond, walking paths, playgrounds & dining areas.
detail_description: Parque de la Paloma is a delightful urban oasis that invites visitors to unwind amidst its lush greenery and serene atmosphere. This spacious park features an artificial pond, meandering walking paths, vibrant playgrounds for children, and charming dining areas perfect for a leisurely meal. It stands out as one of the must-visit attractions in the region, alongside other popular spots like Benalmadena Beaches and Tivoli World Park.
name: Parque de la Paloma
address: Av. Federico García Lorca, s/n, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Benalmádena is a town on southern Spain's Costa del Sol, known for its beaches and Tivoli World theme park. The modern Puerto Marina is home to the Sea Life Benalmádena aquarium and moored yachts. In the traditional Andalusian old town lie the Castillo Monumento Colomares, a castle-style monument dedicated to Christopher Columbus and his discovery of America, and the Benalmádena Stupa, a large Buddhist temple.
detail_description: Benalmádena, located on the Costa del Sol in southern Spain, offers a mix of modern attractions and traditional Andalusian charm. The town is divided into two centers: Benalmadena Pueblo, situated on the hillside, and Benalmadena Costa, a luxurious beach resort with a long stretch of beach and a beautiful marina surrounded by unique architecture.
name: Benalmádena

excerpt: The 15-minute journey up Mount Calamorro in this modern cable car provides spectacular views.
detail_description: Experience the breathtaking Benalmádena Cablecar for an unforgettable journey to the summit of Mount Calamorro. The modern cable car offers stunning aerial views of Benalmádena and its surroundings, ascending to over 700 meters. From the top, visitors are treated to panoramic vistas of the Costa del Sol, with sights stretching from the Mediterranean Sea to Sierra Nevada and even on clear days, the coast of Africa.
name: Benalmádena Cablecar
address: Explanada del Tivoli, s/n, 29631 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Waterfront cultural center with exhibits & special events such as concerts & art shows.
detail_description: Castillo de El-Bil-Bil, also known as Bil Bil Castle, is a striking waterfront cultural center located in Benalmadena Costa. This early 20th-century landmark was built by an Englishman named William Leonard Hunt and features a unique architectural style that blends Moorish and Andalusian design elements. The castle hosts various events such as art exhibitions, concerts, and conferences.
name: Castillo de El-Bil-Bil
address: Av. Antonio Machado, 78, 29631 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Puerto Marina is a charming harbor located just a short 5-minute walk away, offering stunning sea views from most of its rooms. The area is surrounded by numerous bars, restaurants, and shops, creating a pleasant and cozy atmosphere. Visitors can enjoy the beautiful waterfront with plenty of dining options and even a shopping center nearby.
name: Puerto Marina

excerpt: Waterfront plaza boasting posh retailers & restaurants in a relaxed, open-air setting.
detail_description: Puerto Marina Benalmádena Official is a vibrant waterfront plaza featuring upscale shops and dining options in a relaxed, outdoor setting. The area offers diverse nightlife experiences, catering to different crowds with its variety of bars and clubs. This award-winning marina serves as a hub for nautical activities and entertainment, boasting an array of restaurants, bars, shops, and even an aquarium. Its unique architectural style blends Arabic and Andalusian elements, creating a captivating atmosphere for leisurely strolls.
name: Puerto Marina Benalmadena
address: C. La Fragata, A11, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Large Buddhist monument to enlightenment containing a meditation hall & an array of sacred objects.
detail_description: The Stupa of Enlightenment in Benalmádena is a significant Buddhist monument symbolizing peace, prosperity, and harmony. Inaugurated in 2003, it is the largest stupa in the Western World and serves as a place for reflection and meditation. Managed by the Asociacion Cultural Karma Kagyu de Benalmadena, this iconic monument offers access to its inner structure, including a meditation hall with serene surroundings overlooking the coastline.
name: Stupa of Enlightenment Benalmádena
address: Av. Retamar, s/n, 29639 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Arroyo de la Miel, which translates to "river of honey," is a charming village nestled between the mountains and the coast near Benalmadena. This vibrant pueblo boasts a diverse population of local and international residents, as well as a thriving tourist sector. Visitors can explore various attractions such as a sports complex, bilingual library, and the renowned Tivoli World theme park.
name: Arroyo de la Miel

excerpt: This architecturally unique castle-style monument honoring Christopher Columbus offers scenic views.
detail_description: Colomares Castle, located in Benalmadena Pueblo, is a relatively new monument built between 1987 and 1994. Despite its recent construction, the castle exudes an old-world charm and features a unique blend of architectural styles including Mudejar, Gothic, Byzantine, and Romanesque. This makes it the largest monument in the world dedicated to Christopher Columbus. The castle offers breathtaking views as it stands amidst the treetops and white buildings of the skyline.
name: Colomares Castle
address: Finca la Carraca, Ctra. Costa del Sol, s/n, 29639 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Charming museum in a former manor featuring Pre-Columbian art & local archaeological artifacts.
detail_description: The Benalmádena Museum, located in a former manor in the heart of the old town, is a charming attraction that houses the Archaeological Museum. It offers a unique indoor activity focusing on the area's history before Columbus. The museum features local archaeological artifacts dating back to the Bronze Age and an impressive collection of Pre-Columbian art, particularly renowned for its South American pottery.
name: Benalmádena Museum
address: Plaza de las Tres Culturas, 29639 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Benalmádena Golf is a small yet well-designed 9-hole par 3 course with a driving range, offering distances from 40 to 100m, complete with lakes and trees. It features a shaded driving range and ample parking. The facility also provides lessons and has a junior academy available. Additionally, there are club and restaurant facilities on-site, making it an ideal spot for honing one's short game and mid-range accuracy.
name: Benalmádena Golf
address: Ctra. De Arroyo de la Miel a, Pueblo, s/n, 29639 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Popular Mediterranean resort La Carihuela is defined by its summer beach scene, with hutlike outdoor chiringuito bars serving cold beer and classic pescaíto fried fish, alongside upscale Spanish sea-view restaurants. The waterside promenade draws locals and holidaymakers for evening strolls, and rugged headland Punta Gatuna has a quiet lookout spot for sunset views. Flashy modern dance clubs get busy after dark.
detail_description: La Carihuela, a popular Mediterranean resort, is known for its vibrant beach scene and charming outdoor chiringuito bars offering refreshing drinks and traditional pescaíto fried fish. The waterfront promenade attracts both locals and tourists for leisurely evening walks, while Punta Gatuna's rugged headland provides a serene spot to enjoy stunning sunset views. After dark, modern dance clubs come alive with lively entertainment.
name: La Carihuela

detail_description: Puerto Deportivo de Benalmádena is a top-notch marina in Spain, offering a residential area that has attracted numerous tourists to the Costa del Sol. The marina boasts an attractive design and convenient berthing port facilities. It has been honored with the Best Marina of the World award twice, ensuring high tourist activity year-round.
name: Puerto Deportivo de Benalmádena
address: Edificio Capitania, Av. Juan Sebastian Elcano, s/n, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Designed by José “Pepe” Gancedo, this golf club has an 18-hole course & a luxurious clubhouse.
detail_description: Golf Torrequebrada, located near Marbella and Malaga, is a classic course designed by José “Pepe” Gancedo. Opened in 1976, the course seamlessly blends into the natural landscape with over 100 types of trees creating a lush tropical ambiance. The wide fairways and large greens are strategically protected by sand and water hazards.
name: Golf Torrequebrada
address: C. Club de Golf, 1, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Seaside 2,559-ft. Costa Del Sol peak accessed via cable car or path, with views of Africa & caves.
detail_description: Calamorro is a 2,559-ft. peak located in Costa Del Sol, offering stunning views of the coastline from Malaga city to Fuengirola and beyond. Visitors can reach the summit via a cable car ride on the Teleferico, which starts from Tivoli World. Alternatively, they can opt for a 2-3 hour hike to the top. Once there, they can explore exclusive hiking trails showcasing Mediterranean flora and fauna.
name: Calamorro

excerpt: Baroque hilltop church complex built between the 16th & 18th centuries with coast views.
detail_description: Iglesia de Santo Domingo de Guzmán is a stunning hilltop church complex with a Baroque-style architecture dating back to the 16th and 18th centuries. The church boasts an ornate interior with intricate stonework, an impressive bell tower, and elaborate gold leaf altarpiece. Visitors can admire detailed frescoes and religious sculptures adorning the walls and ceilings.
name: Iglesia de Santo Domingo de Guzmán | Benalmádena
address: C. Santo Domingo, 16, 29639 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Playa Arroyo de la Miel is a charming beach with a Blue Flag distinction, ensuring cleanliness and excellent services. It's conveniently located near the center and boasts fine sand and pristine waters. The beach features a flowing stream that provides a safe play area for children. Visitors can enjoy various amenities such as sunbathing, inflatable toys, restaurants, bars, and swimming.
name: Arroyo de la Miel Beach

excerpt: Sandy beach with hammock & lounge rentals, plus views of a Moorish-style castle that's lit at night.
detail_description: Playa de Bil Bil is the main beach in Benalmadena, offering a lively atmosphere and a variety of activities. Visitors can relax on sandy shores with rental hammocks or engage in water sports. The beach provides beautiful views of a Moorish-style castle illuminated at night. Additionally, there are clean facilities and plenty of dining options nearby. With its clean sands and reasonable prices for amenities like sunbeds, Playa de Bil Bil offers an enjoyable experience for both adults and children alike.
name: Playa de Bil Bil

excerpt: Busy, shallow beach in an urban area with numerous amenities including hotels, bars & restaurants.
detail_description: Playa de Santa Ana, located in the Malaga district of Benalmadena beach, is a bustling urban beach with a vibrant atmosphere and plenty of amenities. The picturesque promenade and lively ambiance make it a popular spot for both locals and tourists. Visitors can enjoy delicious seafood and refreshing cocktails at the numerous beach bars and restaurants. With its expansive sandy areas, calm waters, and nearby services, Playa de Santa Ana offers the perfect setting for a day of sunbathing and sea activities.
name: Playa de Santa Ana

detail_description: Nestled on the edge of a cliff, Jardines del Muro is a stunning park that offers visitors an unforgettable experience with its panoramic views of the Mediterranean Sea and majestic mountains. This unique space beautifully blends Moorish and Christian architectural elements, creating distinct sections that each exude their own charm. As you wander through this enchanting garden, you'll discover diverse plant species in both sunny and shaded areas, making it perfect for relaxing or catching up with friends.
name: Jardines del Muro
address: Ctra. Costa del Sol, 1, 29639 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: A popular diving destination, this small, sandy beach with calm waters is surrounded by palm trees.
detail_description: Playa Las Viborillas is a hidden gem located in Benalmadena, offering a tropical paradise with its sandy shores and calm waters. Surrounded by palm trees and nestled in a rocky cove, this picturesque beach provides a tranquil escape perfect for swimming, snorkeling, and diving. It is also popular among naturists due to its secluded location and verdant surroundings. The beach offers amenities such as showers, beach bars, sun loungers for hire, and easy access for the disabled.
name: Playa Las Viborillas

detail_description: Plaza de España is the bustling heart of the town, where many main streets converge. It's a vibrant hub with plenty of bars and restaurants to enjoy. At its center stands the stunning 1785 fountain of Carlos III, while the adjacent 17th century chapel of Saint Sebastian adds to its charm. This lively square is a focal point for local social gatherings and activities.
name: Pl. de España

excerpt: Small crocodile park with guided tours, a cafe & a petting area where visitors can hold a baby croc.
detail_description: Located in Benalmadena, Crocodile Park is a unique attraction that offers guided tours and a petting area where visitors can hold baby crocodiles. The park is home to over 200 crocodiles from various species, including the impressive Big Daddy. Guided tours provide insight into the life cycle and behavior of these reptiles, with opportunities to witness feeding sessions. It's an ideal destination for families and animal enthusiasts looking for an extraordinary experience on the Costa del Sol.
name: TORREMELINOS Crocodile Park

detail_description: Nestled across from the charming Plaza de Espana, Restaurante La Fuente is a culinary gem that promises to tantalize your taste buds. This delightful eatery specializes in innovative dishes, featuring an array of options such as succulent chicken, juicy steaks, and grilled sea bass. Seafood lovers will be particularly enchanted by their signature dish—a hearty seafood casserole that embodies the essence of coastal cuisine.
name: Restaurant La Fuente
address: Pl. de España, 9, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Opened in 1979, this casino with a bar & a restaurant offers poker tournaments & live entertainment.
detail_description: Gran Madrid | Casino Torrequebrada, established in 1979, is a renowned casino featuring a bar and restaurant. It has been a hub for poker tournaments and live entertainment. The venue was home to traditional flamenco shows until October 2013, attracting visitors with high-quality cabaret acts and flamenco displays. Situated between Malaga and Marbella in Benalmadena Costa, it offers easy access to nearby attractions such as golf courses and beaches.
name: Gran Madrid | Casino Torrequebrada
address: Av. del Sol, s/n, 29631 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Puerto Marina Shopping in Spain offers a delightful shopping and dining experience along the marina. With numerous shops, restaurants, and boat trip options, it's a lovely place to explore. Visitors can enjoy various activities such as boat trips, shopping for souvenirs or gifts, and indulging in delicious meals at the many eateries. The area is clean with picturesque views of the marina and provides ample opportunities for leisurely walks and relaxation.
name: Puerto Marina Shopping
address: Puerto Deportivo de Benalmadena, Av. del Puerto Deportivo, s/n, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Torrequebrada is situated alongside the expansive beach, offering a plethora of services and entertainment options. It's renowned for its charming avenues lined with detached houses, making it an ideal spot for leisure activities and relaxation.
name: Torrequebrada

detail_description: Costasol Cruceros offers a thrilling 2-hour boat circuit in the Mediterranean Sea, suitable for groups of 18. The well-maintained two-floor boat features a bar, music, and clean toilets. While a shade on the top floor would be a nice addition, the overall experience is unforgettable. The professional and friendly staff provide informative explanations in multiple languages.
name: Costasol Cruceros - Paseo Delfines y Ferry Benalmádena/Fuengirola
address: C. La Fragata, 6, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Bil Bil Golf is a charming and convenient place to take a break and grab a refreshing drink, with some indulgent treats available as well.
name: Bil Bil Golf
address: Urb. Benalmádena Golf, Av. Cibeles, s/n, 29639 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Just a brief stroll down Calle Felix Solesio will lead you to the serene Plaza de España, a charming little retreat adorned with several authentic bars. Among them, Bar España stands out as one of the finest options for indulging in traditional delights.
name: Plaza de España

detail_description: Sunset Beach Club is one of the renowned beach clubs in Benalmadena, offering a combination of upscale dining, prime location, and an exclusive atmosphere for both relaxation and entertainment against the backdrop of waves and sand. This modern facility also serves as a great hotel option for visitors to the area.
name: Sunset Beach Club

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant town of Benalmadena, Tivoli World stands as a beloved emblem of the Costa del Sol and Andalusia. This enchanting theme park has long been a favorite among locals and tourists alike, offering an array of thrilling rides and attractions that cater to visitors of all ages. Despite facing challenges recently, there is a collective hope for its revival, with dreams of families once again filling its grounds with laughter and joy.
name: Tivoli World

excerpt: Mijas is a municipality in the Province of Málaga, in the autonomous community of Andalusia. Located on the southeastern coast of Spain, Mijas belongs to the region of Costa del Sol Occidental. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Mijas is a charming municipality in the Province of Málaga, Andalusia, situated on the southeastern coast of Spain. Divided into two distinct areas, Mijas Costa offers 12km of beach and holiday resorts with various entertainment options, while Mijas Pueblo is a picturesque village nestled in the hills. The pueblo features rows of white-washed houses adorned with flower pots and pine trees, attracting artists and writers over the years.
name: Mijas

excerpt: Fuengirola is a town on the Costa del Sol in southern Spain, known for its sandy beaches. South of the city center, the medieval Moorish Sohail Castle towers over the coastline, and hosts concerts, festivals and a medieval market in summer. Adjacent to the Plaza de Toros bullring is Bioparc Fuengirola, a naturalistic zoo featuring a re-created jungle clearing and animals from Asia and Africa.
detail_description: Fuengirola, a charming town on the Costa del Sol in southern Spain, is renowned for its beautiful sandy beaches. The city boasts the impressive Sohail Castle, which overlooks the coastline and hosts various events throughout the summer. Additionally, visitors can explore Bioparc Fuengirola, a unique zoo featuring animals from Asia and Africa in a naturalistic setting.
name: Fuengirola

excerpt: Walks & cable-car rides to mountaintop venue featuring eagle presentations & astronomy programs.
detail_description: The Garden of Eagles is an amusement center located atop a mountain that can be reached by taking a cable car ride. Visitors can enjoy watching presentations featuring eagles and learn about astronomy through various programs. The cable car ticket includes access to bird shows, where attendees are treated to an impressive display of the birds' abilities. Trainers at the center speak both Spanish and English, making it accessible for all visitors.
name: Garden Of Eagles

detail_description: 24 Hour Square, situated in the vibrant Benalmadena, is a popular spot best visited around midnight. Geared towards a younger crowd, particularly those in their 20s, it's not recommended for families. Despite some mixed reviews, it offers enjoyable nightlife experiences without being as chaotic as some may suggest.
name: 24 Hour Square

detail_description: Playa de Torre Vigía is a spectacular beach with crystal clear waters, but it's advisable to wear flip flops due to the stones. It's a small beach, so arriving early is recommended. There's a bar called Tulum right on the beach that offers great food. The shore is mostly gravel, so bathing shoes are advisable. Loungers can be rented from around 9 a.m., and there are toilets and a restaurant on site.
name: Playa de Torre Vigía

detail_description: The Hindu temple Templo Hindú is a beautiful, peaceful place of worship where people from all religions are welcome. The temple has decorations and a floor design of the swastika, which is the symbol of well-being. There are also different meditation times available for a few euros, and Namaste is said here frequently.
name: Templo Hindú de Benalmádena

detail_description: Culture House Benalmádena is a vibrant hub of cultural events and activities. From the lively Festival de Verano featuring live music, street theatre, and free beach film screenings during the summer to delightful food festivals showcasing the best seafood in Benalmádena, there's something for everyone. The venue also hosts an impressive theater program with a diverse range of performances including musicals and classic Greek plays.
name: Culture House Benalmádena
address: Plaza Austria, s/n, 29631 Arroyo De La Miel-Benalmádena Costa, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant town of Benalmádena, the Centro de Exposiciones de Benalmádena stands as a beacon for art enthusiasts and culture seekers alike. This dynamic exhibition center was established to integrate the region into both national and international art scenes. With a schedule that features 4 to 5 exhibitions annually, visitors can expect a diverse array of artistic showcases.
name: Centro de Exposiciones de Benalmádena
address: Av. Antonio Machado, 33, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Nestled along the stunning coastline of Benalmadena, Torre Vigía Bermeja stands as a testament to the region's rich history. This watchtower is one of three in the area, alongside Torremuelle and Torrequebrada, and dates back to a time when it served as a lookout against Barbary pirate attacks. The entire Malaga coast is dotted with similar towers, some dating back to the 15th century, showcasing an architectural heritage that deserves preservation.
name: Torre Vigía Bermeja

detail_description: Fuente Salud Beach offers a soft and smooth sand that is perfect for children to play on. The beach is bustling with activity, as it features a pathway leading down to the shore. This section of the beach provides visitors with easy access to enjoy the beautiful coastal scenery and soak up the sun.
name: Fuente Salud Beach
Noria - Mirador Princess
address: Ap, C. La Fragata, s/n, 29631 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

detail_description: Rotonda Los Molinillos is a prominent landmark in Benalmadena Costa, featuring an impressive 18-meter tall sculpture of moving elements. Created by Angel Canizares, known for his work on grand film productions, the sculpture captivates attention with its agility and movement, especially on windy days. Situated near a Roman site with a free interpretation center, it offers insights into the history and archaeological sites of Benalmadena.
name: Rotonda Los Molinillos
address: Av. Antonio Machado, 71, 29630 Benalmádena, Málaga, Spain

excerpt: Accessible urban beach with deck chairs, parasols & sports equipment for hire & a cafe.
detail_description: Playa del Arroyo de la Miel y los Melilleros, also known as Arroyo de la Miel Beach, is a popular urban beach in Benalmadena. It offers accessibility, quality amenities such as deck chairs and parasols for hire, sports equipment rentals, and a beachside cafe. The dark sand beach provides a good entry into the water and is ideal for leisurely walks.
name: Playa del Arroyo de la Miel y los Melilleros

detail_description: Playa de las Verdas is a great spot to visit during the Easter bank holiday weekends. While the sand may not be the smoothest due to shells and rocky terrain, it offers plenty of fun and sun. The beach is not crowded and provides little shade, umbrellas, and loungers. It's a spacious area that is hardly rowdy, making it perfect for families with kids to enjoy a relaxing day by the sea.
name: Playa de las Verdas

detail_description: Playa de Arroyo Hondo is a picturesque beach located in Benalmadena, just a few minutes from the port. It is situated between 'Las Viborillas' and 'Torremuelle' and is named after the river that flows into the sea at this point. The beach offers two parts, one following the natural line of the sea and another wider area that has been regenerated.
name: Playa de Arroyo Hondo
